=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Looking at the mapped SMIRKS transformation:

**Reactant:** C1C[C:20]([OH:10])(O)[OH+:21]C1 — cyclobutane with geminal [OH:10]/[OH+:21] on [C:20]
**Product:** C(C[C:20](=[OH+:10])O)C[OH+:21] — open-chain with carbonyl at [C:20] and [OH+:21] on terminal C

Reaction center bond edits:
- **Broken:** C–C ring bond (between [C:20] and adjacent ring carbon), C:20–OH+:21 single bond
- **Formed:** C(ring terminal)–OH+:21 single bond, C:20=OH+:10 double bond
- **Order change:** C:20–OH:10 single → double

This is a ring-opening fragmentation of a protonated gem-diol cyclobutane, yielding an open-chain aldehyde/ketone with hydroxyl migration.

